    <subfield code="a">• The implementation of the Central Interlock System of the ITER full-size ion source in the Neutral Beam Test Facility is reported. • Fast and slow interlock functions need reaction times faster than 10 μs and 100 ms, respectively. • Slow interlock is implemented by Siemens PLCs and WinCC OA SCADA. • Fast interlock is implemented by National Instruments CompactRIO.</subfield>
